      "side": 1,
      "message": "The Uart has a FIFO which is enabled by default (line 331), so it would be better to read until the FIFO is not empty and buf is not full. The Uart should be responsible for keeping the FIFO level as low as possible to prevent overruns. The function would still only block until the first available read but if there\u0027s already more data in the FIFO, it should read as much as it can.\nIf you agree with this reasoning, the embedded_io::Write should also follow the same pattern to maximize throughput.",
      "revId": "068398e1aa2c8534a56cb17f872250bd99f76f72",
      "serverId": "8f6f209b-db1a-4cbf-aa44-c8bc30e9bfda"
    },
